OL,5,Cclaims
OL,7,FPeston asked the former prime minister
OL,8,Fif he would be happy to swear on oath
OL,9,Fthat the allegations against him were
OL,10,Funtrue. "Absolutely," he said without
OL,11,Fhesitation.
OL,13,FBrown has been concerned for some time
OL,14,Fthat not only his privacy, but also
OL,15,Fthat of his family, was invaded by
OL,16,Fthese newspapers. So, why hasn't he
OL,17,Fever taken action?
